DHCP (dynamic Host Configuration Protocol, Network protocol that automatically assings IP addresses and other configuration 
parameters to dvices on a network

DORA (discover offer request ack)

DHCP happens on startup BOOTP (bios)

discover is sent via broadcast to identify the dhcp server, client initiates
Offer is sent over as unicast, contains available IPs, Lease info, DNS server configs and a default gateway.
Request Packet is sent via broadcast, request to use the obtained offer. this information needs to be known 
to all hosts so IPs are appropiately updated
Acknowledge sent by unicast as confirmation

utilzes udp for the port works with layer 7 and 4
use lease times in seconds, establish a pool with subnet mask
